SIMPLE: sooth
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sooth
<hw>Sooth</hw> <pr>(s⟦oomac⟧th)</pr>, <pos>a.; <plain>also</plain>
adv.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Soother</adjf>
<pr>(s⟦oomac⟧th"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Soothest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>soth</ets>, AS.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>, for <ets>san⟦edh⟧</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>, OHG. <ets>sand</ets>, Icel. <ets>sannr</ets>,
Sw. <ets>sann</ets>, Dan. <ets>sand</ets>, Skr. <ets>sat</ets>,
<ets>sant</ets>, real, genuine, present, being; properly p. pr. from a
root meaning, to be, Skr. <ets>as</ets>, L. <ets>esse</ets>; also akin
to Goth. <ets>sunjis</ets> true, Gr. <grk>'eteo`s</grk>, Skr.
<ets>satya</ets>. ⟦root⟧9. Cf. <er>Absent</er>, <er>Am</er>,
<er>Essence</er>, <er>Is</er>, <er>Soothe</er>, <er>Sutee</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>True; faithful; trustworthy.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sentence [meaning] of it <qex>sooth</qex> is, out of
doubt.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That shall I <qex>sooth</qex> (said he) to you declare.</q>
<rj><qau>Spensser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pleasing; delightful; sweet.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>soothest</qex> shepherd that ever piped on plains.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With jellies <qex>soother</qex> than the creamy curd.</q>
<rj><qau>Keats.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sooth</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sooth
<hw>Sooth</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>s⟦omac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>. See
<er>Sooth</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Truth;
reality.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>sooth</qex> it this, the cut fell to the knight.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In <qex>sooth</qex>, I know not why I am so sad.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In good <qex>sooth</qex>,⟦br⟧
Its mystery is love, its meaninng youth.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Augury; prognostication.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>soothe</qex> of birds by beating of their wings.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Blandishment; cajolery.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soothe</ent>⟦br⟧
